This page contains '''Resources''' to help guide you, using official VRChat outlets.

== VRChat website == <!--T:3-->

=== Hello! === <!--T:4-->

<!--T:5-->
* {{VRC link|https://hello.vrchat.com|hello.vrchat.com}}
** {{VRC link|https://hello.vrchat.com/blog|VRChat's Blog}}

<!--T:6-->
This is VRChat's primary home website, and serves as a main hub to VRChat's resources and services. Users can also choose to log in with their [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat account|VRChat account]], to access and manage their profile, friends, and more.

== Support resources == <!--T:7-->

<!--T:8-->
[[File:VRC Support Banner.png|thumb]]
[[File:How to Contact Support.png|thumb|288x288px]]

===Help Forum=== <!--T:9-->

<!--T:10-->
* {{VRC link|https://help.vrchat.com|help.vrchat.com}}

<!--T:11-->
VRChat's Help Forum, also known as their "Knowledge Base", is implemented to assist users in solving problems that they may be facing with the platform. You can use this website to search for guides to help you with an issue, submit support requests, or moderation [[Special:MyLanguage/Reporting|reports]].

<!--T:12-->
VRChat's support team, or [[Special:MyLanguage/Trust and Safety|Trust and Safety]] team will assist you with your issue, if you submit a support request or moderation ticket. Support and moderation tickets that can be submitted under these categories:

<!--T:13-->
* Support Requests
* Moderation Reports / Appeals
* Avatar Marketplace Help
* Locked Account Recovery
* Security Exploit Reports
* Copyright Infringement Reports

===Ask Forum=== <!--T:14-->

<!--T:15-->
* [https://ask.vrchat.com ask.vrchat.com]

<!--T:16-->
VRChat's Ask Forum is a community forum that allows users to ask questions, and browse posts by the Community on various boards, and browse VRChat '[[Developer Update|Developer Updates]]', and 'Official Notes' created by the VRChat Team. The various boards that can be browsed and posted or commented to, are the following:

<!--T:17-->
* Help! board
* Official board
* General Discussion board
* Creator Hub board
* Tutorials, Tools, and Resources board  

===Status Page=== <!--T:18-->

<!--T:19-->
* {{VRC link|https://status.vrchat.com|status.vrchat.com}}
** [https://x.com/VRChat_Status @VRChat_Status] on ''X.com''

<!--T:20-->
The Status website, powered by Atlassian Statuspage<ref>[https://www.atlassian.com/software/statuspage 'Atlassian Statuspage - Official website'] at ''atlassian.com''; retrieved September 15, 2025.</ref> presents data, regarding the server statuses of VRChat's services and [[Special:MyLanguage/Instance|Instances]]. This page shows schedules for upcoming server maintenance, the operational statuses and recent incidents for the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat API|VRChat API]], and the website, for the following data:

<!--T:21-->
* Realtime Networking
** USA, West (San José) 
** USA, East (Washington D.C.)
** Europe (Amsterdam)
** Japan (Tokyo)

<!--T:22-->
* API/Website
** Authentication and Login
** Social and Friends List
** SDK Asset Uploads
** Realtime Player State Changes
*** Avatar switching, status changes, etc.

<!--T:23-->
This page also demonstrates graphs of networking traffic for VRChat, such as online user count, API latency, API requests, Steam authentication success rate, and Meta authentication success rate.

==Feedback== <!--T:24-->

<!--T:25-->
[[File:Submit Feedback and Bug Reports.png|thumb|288x288px]]

<!--T:26-->
''See also [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat Feedback|VRChat Feedback]] for more detailed information.''

<!--T:27-->
* {{VRC link|https://feedback.vrchat.com|feedback.vrchat.com}}

<!--T:28-->
'''VRChat's Feedback Forums''', powered by Canny.io, consists of several community boards. Community Feedback is always welcome. 

<!--T:29-->
Please post feedback on relevant boards, for posts regarding bug reports, feature requests, community feedback, and tracking implementation of new features. Upvoting posts on these boards, helps make suggestions more prioritized by the VRChat Team.

==Documentation== <!--T:30-->

<!--T:31-->
VRChat's Documentation covers official notations on implemented features, patchnotes, changelogs, and [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat SDK|VRChat SDK]] framework. The VRChat documentation also covers guides, and [[Special:MyLanguage/Frequently Asked Questions|Frequently Asked Questions]].

<!--T:32-->
The Creator Documentation covers documentation regarding the VRChat SDK, [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat Creator Companion|VRChat Creator Companion]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Worlds|Worlds]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Udon|Udons]], [[Special:MyLanguage/Avatars|Avatars]], and [[Special:MyLanguage/Creator Economy|Creator Economy]]. This page also covers upcoming 'creator roadmap' features to be implemented, and recent releases for the VRChat SDK.

